# Trivy allowlist — accepted vulnerability exceptions.
#
# Format: one CVE per line, optional `# reason — yyyy-mm-dd` after.
# Empty by default. Add only after weighing the exposure:
#   - Is the vulnerable code path actually reachable from our usage?
#   - Is there a justified reason not to upgrade (e.g. major-version breaker)?
#   - Has the upstream maintainer acknowledged + scheduled a fix?
#
# Anything here gets re-reviewed quarterly — leaving entries to rot defeats
# the point of the scan. Prefer upgrading deps over allowlisting.
